in which each signal charge stored at a pixel’s photodiode is shifted to a vertical CCD
(V-CCD) simultaneously over the entire imaging array and is then transferred from
the V-CCD to the horizontal CCD (H-CCD). The charge within the H-CCD is trans-
ferred to the output amplifer, which converts it into a voltage signal. The charge
transfer readout scheme requires almost perfect charge transfer effciency, which, in
turn, requires highly tuned semiconductor structures and process technology.
